The paper discusses the development of Generative Temporal Models augmented with external memory systems, which are used to model temporal data with long-range dependencies. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the development of a new type of model for temporal data, rather than on specific applications or datasets, we believe that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
